National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has assured of President Muhammadu Buhari’s determination to use all means necessary to end banditry and other forms of insecurities. Tinubu spoke when he paid a condolence visit to Katsina Governor Aminu Bello Masari at Government House on Sunday over the gruesome murder of Commissioner of Science, Technology and Innovation, Dr Rabe Nasir as well as the recent upsurge of insecurity in the State. He said: ’’Let’s be vigilant, help our country, preach peace and remain determined to end the evil inflicted upon us by terrorism. ‘’Buhari government will use all means necessary to bring banditry and insecurity to an end.   AFCON 2021: Sierra Leone in dramatic injury-time equaliser…     Osimhen ready for comeback after injury, COVID-19     Osun 2022: Ogunbiyi denies alliance with Adeleke   ‘’We are going to support the President to bring to an end the evil caused by terrorism, we will continue to identify with you to conquer this evil.” - Advertisement - He further asked Katsina citizens to share relevant information with security agencies on suspicious movements of characters and persons. The former Lagos Governor described the late Commissioner as a reliable person and man of integrity Governor Masari welcomed the APC stalwart, saying his visit demonstrated the love he has for Katsina people.